docs.abstract: After her divorce from the Amazon founder and chief executive Jeff Bezos was announced earlier this year, Ms. Bezos has pledged away more than half of her wealth in committing to the Giving Pledge.
docs.snippet: After her divorce from the Amazon founder and chief executive Jeff Bezos was announced earlier this year, Ms. Bezos has pledged away more than half of her wealth in committing to the Giving Pledge.
docs.lead_paragraph: MacKenzie Bezos has promised to give more than half of her fortune to charity as part of the Giving Pledge, the organization said Tuesday. Ms. Bezos, whose divorce from the Amazon founder and chief executive Jeff Bezos made news earlier this year, was among 19 new signatories announced by the group.

headline.main: MacKenzie Bezos Owns $36 Billion in Amazon Shares. Now She Is Vowing to Give Away Much of Her Wealth.
headline.print_headline: Amazon Founder’s Ex-Wife to Give Billions to Charity

docs.abstract: “A Rainy Day in New York,” starring Timothée Chalamet and Elle Fanning, will be released in Italy on Oct. 3. German and Spanish distributors have confirmed they are releasing it.
docs.snippet: “A Rainy Day in New York,” starring Timothée Chalamet and Elle Fanning, will be released in Italy on Oct. 3. German and Spanish distributors have confirmed they are releasing it.
docs.lead_paragraph: Woody Allen’s latest movie, “A Rainy Day in New York,” a romantic comedy starring Timothée Chalamet and Elle Fanning, was dropped by Amazon last year. There is no sign it will be released in the United States.

headline.main: Amazon Dropped Woody Allen’s Latest Film. Europe Has Picked It Up.
headline.print_headline: Woody Allen Film Gets European Release

docs.abstract: Three women near Minneapolis argue that Amazon retaliated against them after they protested their working conditions.
docs.snippet: Three women near Minneapolis argue that Amazon retaliated against them after they protested their working conditions.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Three Somali women working for Amazon near Minneapolis have accused the company of creating a hostile environment for Muslim workers and of retaliating against them for protesting their work conditions, according to a filing submitted this week to federal regulators.

headline.main: 3 Muslim Workers at Amazon File Federal Discrimination Complaint
